 is coming, and my poor fingers just can't write fast enough.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Years went by, Gkako trained and hunted in the nearby swamps.  She learned the secrets of Fear, and embraced them.<br>
<br>
<br>
She was now looked upon by her people as a hero, her parents were proud.  Hukulk had even smiled upon her after she had turned in her last bag of frogluk legs.<br>
<br>
&quot;Gkako, you brave!  Yu take mes wif you da next time, me can give yous da wolfie feets now!&quot;  Ghunk said when he saw her return from her hunt.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ghunk!  Me lik that.  You and me can barsh froggies!  Me get some sleep, we'll go out in the morning.&quot;  Gkako, said, truly pleased to see him again.  After the last time she had seen him he was her only regret.  They had not truly parted friends that day, but hopefully that would change.  She missed his company.<br>
<br>
&quot;You no sound like Gkako.  You start sound like deem tiny darkies.&quot;  Ghunk said suspiously.  He never truly trusted the Dark Elves that visited Grobb.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ghunk, those darkies, dey good thinkers.  Me talk, they listen.  Dey heads no hurt, dey say, 'Yes, Gkako, you are right.  That is a good idea.'  But ghunk, we talk next day, I'm tired.  Me smelly like froggies.&quot;   gkako smiled at her friend, knowing that tomarrow would be a wonderful day.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ok, Gkako, me see yous in da day.&quot;  Ghunk waved and went into his hut.<br>
<br>
The next morning the two friends sat in the swamp and talked of their different life paths, they shared memories, and even got to bash some frogs.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ghunk, you want go home?  Or we could go over to dat hill and see if more froggies there.&quot;  Gkako asked him, hoping he would want to continue their adventure.  She was having more fun today, than she had in a long time.  Sometimes, the path of Fear was lonley.<br>
<br>
&quot;We go to hill, we bring more froggie legs.  We be big heroes!&quot;  Ghunk laughed.<br>
<br>
As the two friends weent ove rthe hill they were attacked by a swarm of elves.  High Elves chanting powerful spells, Wood elves shooting arrows and swinging swords.  The two trolls were outnumbered.<br>
<br>
Gkako heard ghunk scream behind her, calling upon her dark powers, she touched the cheek of the Wood elf she had been fighting.  It's scream of pain and fear died in it's thoat, as it's body fell lifeless into the myrky waters.  Turning, she saw Ghunk fall, with arrows stickiing out of his body.<br>
<br>
She never saw the Paladin swing his mighty Ghoulbane.  She only saw blackness.<br>
